{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 45521140, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-MEDIA-EE24", "title": "Media actions EE24", "publicationDateLong": 1666828800000, "callIdentifier": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-MEDIA", "callTitle": "Call for grants for media actions in the area of communication ahead of the 2024 European Elections", "callccm2Id": 45521147, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43697167, "abbreviation": "EP", "description": "European Parliament"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43697187, "abbreviation": "EP-1-1", "description": "Grants in the Area of Communication"}], "topicMGAs": [], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094502, "abbreviation": "Open", "description": "Open"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43694065, "abbreviation": "EP-AG", "description": "EP Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "27 October 2022", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["26 January 2023"]}], "latestInfos": [], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3420688": [{"action": "EP-COMM-SUBV-2022-MEDIA-EE24 - EP-PJG EP Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "27 October 2022", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["26 January 2023"], "budgetYearMap": {"2023": 8000000}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2023"]}, "description": "<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Objective</SPAN>:<p>These media actions must have a two-fold objective:</p><p>1. Providing <strong>regular, reliable, pluralistic and non-partisan information</strong> on the forthcoming 2024 European Elections, as well as on the political and legislative work of the European Parliament (inter alia: recovery plan Next Generation EU, European Green Deal, European Digital Economy, Europe in the world, Future of Europe, rule of law, etc.), emphasizing its implications in the European citizen\u2019s daily lives.</p><p>2. <strong>Promoting participation and engaging</strong> citizens and civil society organisations in the debate on the forthcoming 2024 European Elections, by organising online and off-line events, public consultations, surveys, etc.</p>\n<SPAN class=\"topicdescriptionkind\">Scope</SPAN>:<p>This is a call for EU action grants for communication activities in the field of media managed by the DG Communication of the European Parliament, ahead of the 2024 European Elections.</p><p>The purpose of this call for proposal is to award grants co-financing media actions by news agencies, television channels, radio stations, digital media and written press. Digital media includes both digital-only media and digital platforms of other media.</p>\n", "conditions": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Conditions</span></b><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:&#10;text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">1.&nbsp;</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Admissibility conditions: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 6 of the call document</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Proposal page limits and layout:</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\"> described in Part B of the Application Form available in the Submission System<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">2. Eligible countries: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in section 7.3 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">3. Other eligibility conditions:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\"> described in section 7 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p><b>4. Financial and operational capacity and exclusion: </b><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">described in </span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">section 8 of the call document</span><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p><b><span lang=\"FR-BE\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:FR-BE\">5.&nbsp;Evaluation and award:</span></b><span lang=\"FR-BE\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:FR-BE\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<ul>\r\n    <li>&nbsp;<b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Award criteria, scoring and thresholds:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;described in section 10 of the call document</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">Submission and evaluation processes</span></b><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">:</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;described&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">section 9 of the call document and the</span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/common/guidance/om_en.pdf\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Online Manual</span></a></li>\r\n</ul>\n<p><span id=\"1617195973454S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"1617195972667S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Indicative timeline for      evaluation and grant agreement: </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">described in      section 5 of the call document<o:p></o:p></span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<p><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\">6</span></b><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:no